<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-01T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/1246a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-01T19:00:00-05:00">November 1, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>826. At request of David MeKelvey White of Friends of Abraham Lincoln
                            Brigade, please report circumstances of and basic reason for reported
                            action of French authorities in refusing admission to group of wounded
                            Americans from Spain.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>